            <entry xml:id="entry_æng0yrstwan" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æng˳yrstwan</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ængurstewan</orth><form
                        type="variant"><orth>ængurstewnæ</orth></form><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>ængurstawnæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>наперсток</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>thimble</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Sajnæg-ældary ḱyzg kærdǵæ-xujgæ kæny, jæ sūʒīn æmæ je ʽng˳yrstwan
                            tævd kænync, īxǵyn don jæ cūry dary, æmæ sæ ūcy ran tūly</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>дочь Сайнаг-алдара кроит-шьет, ее игла и наперсток накаляются, она
                                держит возле себя ледяную воду и туда их погружает</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Sajnag-aldar’s daughter is cutting-sewing, her niddle and thimble are
                                becoming hot, she has ice-cold water near her and she is dipping
                                them there</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            98</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>konǧædæ æ soʒīnæ, fæstæ je ʽngurstewæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>бревно (служит) ей иглой, ступа — наперстком</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a beam serves her as a niddle, a mortar serves as a thimble</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 108</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*angušta-pāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>покрышка пальца</q></gloss></mentioned> (%ipānа%i- от корня
                    %ipā%i- ‘оберегать’, ‘прикрывать’, см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæjnæg"/>),
                    ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>anguštpana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><w>anguštbān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>anguštwāna</w>
                        <gloss><q>наперсток</q></gloss></mentioned>. Наличное в ос. %ir%i —
                    результат контаминации с другим вариантом *%iangur%i- ‘палец’, наличным в <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_æng0ylʒ"/> ‘палец’. Возможно заимствование из
                    персидского; но через какое посредство?%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*angušta-pāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>finger-cover</q></gloss></mentioned> (%ipānа%i- is derived from
                    the root %ipā%i- ‘to protect’, ‘to cover’, see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_fæjnæg"/>), compare <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>anguštpana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><w>anguštbān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>anguštwāna</w>
                        <gloss><q>thimble</q></gloss></mentioned>. There is an %ir%i in Ossetic
                    because of contamination with the other variant *%iangur%i- ‘finger’, which is
                    found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æng0ylʒ"/> ‘finger’. Probably, it is a
                    loan word from Persian, but what language was a mediation part?%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                        /><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
